parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause the check engine light to illuminate, indicating a problem with the engine.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the engine stalls
the engine warning sign blinks or stays on
the vehicle stops running
and the camshaft position sensor malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, and can also lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle stops running
broken pistons
bent valves
loose gas pedal
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address recall issues can lead to accidents or engine failure, and dealer unresponsiveness can leave consumers without a solution to their problems.
symptoms: Consumers receive recall notices but dealerships do not have the necessary parts or refuse to perform the recall
dealerships are not in operation
and consumers are unable to find a dealership to perform the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm can cause the vehicle to jerk or vibrate, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates
the tires wear unevenly
the control arm makes a cracking noise
the vehicle jerks to one side
the front end makes a squeaking noise
the control arm bushings wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the emergency brake is frozen
the vehicle does not move in reverse.
